2026-05-15 | Find Minimum in Rotated Sorted Array

	Question
Return minimum element in rotated array.
	Key Insight
In rotated sorted array:
		one half is always sorted  
The minimum lies in the unsorted half.
Using binary search:
- compare mid with rightmost element  
If nums[mid] > nums[right]:
		minimum is in right half  
Else:
		minimum is in left half including mid
	Approach
1.	Initialize:
		left = 0
		right = n-1  
2.	While left < right:
		find mid  
3.	If nums[mid] > nums[right]:
		search right half  
4.	Else:
		search left half including mid  
5.	Finally:
		left points to minimum  
	Time Complexity
	O(log n)
	Space Complexity
	O(1)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    int findMin(vector<int>& nums) {
        int left = 0;
        int right = nums.size() - 1;
        while(left < right){
            int mid = left + (right - left) / 2;
            if(nums[mid] > nums[right]){
                left = mid + 1;
            }
            else{
                right = mid;
            }
        }
        return nums[left];
    }
};
	Key Insight
The rotated array always has:
		one sorted half
		and one disrupted half  
The minimum element lies where rotation happened,
and binary search efficiently locates it.
